\name{CompetingRisk-package}
\alias{CompetingRisk-package}
\alias{CompetingRisk}
\docType{package}
\title{
Evaluating Prognostic Markers under Competing Risk 
}
\description{

This package aims to help to evaluate the prognostic accuracy of a marker with multiple competing risk events. 

Functions to calculate the AUC, ROC, PPV, and NPV are provided. A discrete covariate Z, if available, can be included. 

}
\details{
\tabular{ll}{
Package: \tab CompetingRisk\cr
Type: \tab Package\cr
Version: \tab 1.1\cr
Date: \tab 2012-06-22\cr
License: \tab What license is it under?\cr
}
There are five main functions in this package:

1. comprisk.ROC:    Calculate the values needed to plot the ROC curve, along with the AUC. 

2. comprisk.ROC.CI: Calculate bootstrap confidence intervals for a given set of TPR or FPR values.

3. comprisk.AUC.CI: Calculate bootstrap confidence intervals for the AUC. 

4. comprisk.PPV:    Calculate PPV and NPV values. 

5. comprisk.PPV.CI: Calculate bootstrap confidence intervals for a given set of PPV, NPV, or v (marker quantile). 
  
}
\author{
Marshall Brown and Yingye Zheng

mdbrown@fhcrc.org
}
